Hi, I use Electron and Angular and I noticed two different behaviour between macOS and Windows when a component has the `drop` and `focus` event.

```
  @HostListener('window:focus', ['$event'])
  onFocus(event: any): void {
    console.log('focus');
  }
  @HostListener('drop', ['$event'])
  onDrop(event: any): void {
    console.log('drop');
  }
```

If I drag a directory onto the browser window on macOS I only get a `drop` in the console. On Windows however I get between 1 and 2 `focus` outputs before. Is this intended? And if so, what are potential workarounds? I need to distinguish between a real focus and a drop event.

Any help is highly appreciated!

